Diff Between @RestController vs @Controller


@RestController
-It returns data directly in response body.
-No need of ViewResolver.
-It is combination of @Controller & @ResponseBody

@Controller
-It return view name.
-It uses a viewResolver to resolve a template (eg Html or Jsp) from view name.
-Need explicitly use @ResponseBody to bypass ViewResolver and send data directly. (It has only @Controller if we want to return data we need to exaplicitly need to add @responsebody annotation) 

ViewResolver is an interface that maps view names return by controllers to actual view files


