Difference Between Spring vs SpringBoot

Spring boot:

-Provides auto configuration.  Ex - database configuration, tomcate configuration, dispatcher servlet configuration.
-It has embeded tomcat server.
-It provide support for in-memory database such as H2.
-It manage dependancy version for you.


-All the code and beans already written in jars by java we just need to add the dependancy of releative jar if we add that dependancies java automatic configure and create beans which are difine in that class on the basis of conditional annotation which are present in that class ,all the auto configure classes have @AutoConfiguration annotation present which execute as per conditions


########################################################################################################################################################################

@SpringBootApplication annotation

Consist Combination of below 3 annotations
1.@SpringBootConfiguration - when put on a class makes that class a source for a bean declarations.
2.@EnableAutoConfiguration - enable auto configuration
3.@ComponentScan - scans your project, looks out for declared beans and actually create those beans in IOC container.

